Create Calculated Fields. 8
Calculated fields allow you to create new data from data that already exists in your data source. We can use Calculated Fields in the same as the dimensions and measures from the source data.

Create Calculated field gif 


Follow the above steps to create each of these calculated Fields. - Formulas are given below: (Name, Formula). 
Note: - This is a process, take time to keenly and systematically create the fields. This helps you have the required fields ready for visualization.
              - For this Step there is an option to use attached file to copy the formulas especially the Up and Down Indicators  which come as "?" on the platform click the icon above to download and access the formulas (with actual indicators).  

Max Year Calculation

cc.Max Date

{FIXED : MAX([Year])}


Current Year and Previous Year Calculations

cc.CY Units Available

SUM(IF YEAR([Year]) = YEAR([cc.Max Date])

THEN  [Units Available] END)

 

cc.PY Units Available

SUM(IF YEAR([Year]) = YEAR([cc.Max Date]) - 1

THEN  [Units Available] END)

 

cc.CY Applicants

SUM(IF YEAR([Year]) = YEAR([cc.Max Date])

THEN [Applicants] END)

 

cc.PY Applicants

SUM(IF YEAR([Year]) = YEAR([cc.Max Date]) - 1

THEN [Applicants] END)

 

cc.CY Avg HH Income

AVG(IF YEAR([Year]) = YEAR([cc.Max Date])

THEN [Household Income] END)

 

cc.PY Avg HH Income

AVG(IF YEAR([Year]) = YEAR([cc.Max Date])-1

THEN [Household Income] END)

 

 cc.CY Mths Waiting

AVG(IF YEAR(Year)= YEAR([cc.Max Date])

THEN [Months Waiting] END)

 

cc.PY Mths Waiting

AVG(IF YEAR(Year)= YEAR([cc.Max Date]) - 1

THEN [Months Waiting] END)



 Year Over Year Calculations

cc.YoY Units Available

ABS(([cc.CY Units Available] - [cc.PY Units Available])

/  [cc.PY Units Available])

 

cc.YoY Applicants

ABS(([cc.CY Applicants]- [cc.PY Applicants])/[cc.PY Applicants])

 

cc.YoY Avg HH Income

(([cc.CY Avg HH Income]- [cc.PY Avg HH Income])/[cc.PY Avg HH Income])

 

cc.YoY Mths Waiting

(([cc.CY Mths Waiting]- [cc.PY Mths Waiting])/[cc.PY Mths Waiting])




UP and Down Indicators Calculations        

cc.YoY Units UP

IF (([cc.CY Units Available] - [cc.PY Units Available]) /[cc.PY Units Available]) > 0 THEN "?" END

 

cc.YoY Units DOWN

IF (([cc.CY Units Available] - [cc.PY Units Available]) /[cc.PY Units Available]) <= 0 THEN "?" END

 

cc.YoY Applicants UP

IF (([cc.CY Applicants]- [cc.PY Applicants])/[cc.PY Applicants]) > 0 THEN "?" END

 

cc.YoY Applicants DOWN

IF (([cc.CY Applicants]- [cc.PY Applicants])/[cc.PY Applicants]) <= 0 THEN "?" END

 

cc.YoY HH Income UP

IF (([cc.CY Avg HH Income]- [cc.PY Avg HH Income])/[cc.PY Avg HH Income]) > 0 THEN "?" END

 

cc.YoY HH Income DOWN

IF (([cc.CY Avg HH Income]- [cc.PY Avg HH Income])/[cc.PY Avg HH Income]) <= 0 THEN "?" END

 

cc.YoY Mths Waiting UP

IF (([cc.CY Mths Waiting]- [cc.PY Mths Waiting])/[cc.PY Mths Waiting]) > 0 THEN "?" END

 

 cc.YoY Mths Waiting DOWN

IF (([cc.CY Mths Waiting]- [cc.PY Mths Waiting])/[cc.PY Mths Waiting]) <= 0 THEN "?" END




More Calculations

cc.Income Brackets

IF [Household Income] <= 10000 THEN '0-10k'

   ELSEIF [Household Income] > 10000 AND [Household Income] <=15000 THEN '10k-15k'

   ELSEIF [Household Income] > 15000 AND [Household Income]<= 20000  THEN '15k-20k'

ELSE '> 20k' END



Reset

"Reset All Filters"



Date Value - Year of Date




Parameter  - Empty Parameter



Region & State

IF [Empty Parameter] = [Region] THEN [State]

ELSE [Region] END
